      "message": "@jcgregorio may have more, but here\u0027s from my perspective:\nCompare using os/exec.Cmd.StdinPipe() (returns a WriteCloser) and doing the same thing with //go/go/exec.Command. In the former, I just start writing and then close it when done. For the latter, I have to set up my own bytes.Buffer (or something) and pass it in.\n\nSimilar extra steps are needed for dealing standard out and error.",
